image.altText: Steph Catley

items.synopsis: The Matildas put the rest of the tournament on notice with a clinical 4-0 victory over Canada in the Women's World Cup in Melbourne. Follow live.

title.children: Matildas score stunning 4-0 victory over Canada to progress into the World Cup round of 16

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: They top Group B and stay alive in the 2023 World Cup! Phenomenal performance when they needed it most. Sam Kerr was not even needed, and will have more time to work on her recovery. Canada, the Olympic champions, go home. I can't pick out a player who underperformed in this game, from Arnold at the back to Foord and Fowler up front. Hayley Raso was the player of the match, with her two goals and energetic involvement throughout.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: FULL-TIME: Matildas 4 - 0 Canada

children.content: They top Group B and stay alive in the 2023 World Cup!
Phenomenal performance when they needed it most.
Sam Kerr was not even needed, and will have more time to work on her recovery.
Canada, the Olympic champions, go home.
I can't pick out a player who underperformed in this game, from Arnold at the back to Foord and Fowler up front.
Hayley Raso was the player of the match, with her two goals and energetic involvement throughout.
(Getty)

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Same spot as the last one - Catley completes the rout! She's not bad at those. And that takes any spice out of the last few minutes, with this one well and truly killed off.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 90+4' Catley steps up - GOAAAAL MATILDAS

children.content: (Getty)
Same spot as the last one - Catley completes the rout!
She's not bad at those.
And that takes any spice out of the last few minutes, with this one well and truly killed off.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: It's Caitlin Foord down the left, crossing low for Fowler, and the young striker gets some kind of contact on it to deflect it onto the post and in. She scuffed that kick a bit, but a goal is a goal. Mary looked a little sheepish after that one. But nobody's ruling it out this time. And Foord deserves so much credit for that goal, dragging defenders towards her before cutting it back.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 58' FOWLER SCORES! That's 3-0 Australia

image.altText: Ben Stokes reviews a decision while Steve Smith talks to England fielders

items.synopsis: Australia needs to pull off the eighth highest successful run chase of all time on the final day of the final Ashes Test at The Oval to win the series outright. Follow live.

title.children: Smith survives controversial Stokes non-catch as Australia eyes historic run chase

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Plenty of words being exchanged as the teams head off the field, none of it too heated, but I think Ben Stokes is unhappy about losing the review. Ben, you knew you dropped it, but you still reviewed. It absolutely has to be lost. What a session. Australia lost three wicket, could've easily lost Travis Head to Stuart Broad or Mark Wood any number of times, and then the Steve Smith/Ben Stokes incident. Crikey, can this series just chill. Anyway, this pair has put on 69 runs, taking Australia within 146 runs of victory at lunch. Fair warning there's rain on the way.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: LUNCH: Australia 3-238 (Smith 40, Head 31)

props.alt: Ben Stokes and Travis Head talk during an Ashes Test.

children.content: (Getty)
Plenty of words being exchanged as the teams head off the field, none of it too heated, but I think Ben Stokes is unhappy about losing the review.
Ben, you knew you dropped it, but you still reviewed. It absolutely has to be lost.
What a session.
Australia lost three wicket, could've easily lost Travis Head to Stuart Broad or Mark Wood any number of times, and then the Steve Smith/Ben Stokes incident.
Crikey, can this series just chill.
Anyway, this pair has put on 69 runs, taking Australia within 146 runs of victory at lunch.
Fair warning there's rain on the way.
